<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Salutation" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Salutation,</orth> a greeting: <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.38" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 1, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.4.39" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 4, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.2.53" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 2, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.4.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 4, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 5.8.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. V, 8, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.4.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 4, 32</bibl>. <cit><quote>to do s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.210" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 3, 210</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.2.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 2, 5</bibl>. <cit><quote>why should others' false adulterate eyes give s. to my sportive blood?</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 121.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 121, 6</bibl></cit> (== affect in any manner, gratify or mortify. cf. the verb <emph>salute,</emph> and <emph>greet</emph> in <bibl n="shak. per 4.3.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 3, 38</bibl>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>